The Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) has constituted its National Campaign Council for the Ekiti State governorship poll. The election will be held on Saturday June 18, 2022. The PDP named Oyo State Governor, Seyi Makinde as the council chairman. National Publicity Secretary, Debo Ologunagba said Abia Governor, Okezie Ikpeazu will serve as his deputy. The spokesmanâ€™s statement on Thursday listed Adedamola Adegbite as the administrative secretary. Council members are Governors Nyesom Wike, Udom Emmanuel, Amb. Taofeek Arapaja and Sen. Samuel Anyanwu, among others. The party will announce the date for the inaugural meeting and other information in due course.